    {
      "title": "Tamyīz (التمييز)",
      "titleArabic": "التمييز",
      "content": [
        "Tamyīz (specification) is a noun that specifies and clarifies a vague concept. It removes ambiguity from words indicating quantity, measure, or comparison."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Always indefinite and singular",
        "Always manṣūb (accusative)",
        "Two types: tamyīz al-dhāt (after quantities) and tamyīz al-nisba (sentence specification)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "عِنْدِي عِشْرُونَ كِتَابًا", "english": "I have twenty books" },
        { "arabic": "اِشْتَرَيْتُ رِطْلًا عَسَلًا", "english": "I bought a pound of honey" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Types of Tamyīz",
      "titleArabic": "أنواع التمييز",
      "content": [
        "Tamyīz al-dhāt specifies after quantity words (numbers, measures, weights). Tamyīz al-nisba (or al-jumla) specifies vague meaning in a sentence."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Tamyīz al-dhāt: after numbers 11-99, measures, weights",
        "Tamyīz al-nisba: with comparatives, expressions of wonder",
        "Example with comparative: هُوَ أَكْبَرُ مِنِّي سِنًّا",
        "Example with 'āmil: طَابَ الْمَكَانُ هَوَاءً"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "هُوَ أَكْبَرُ مِنِّي سِنًّا", "english": "He is older than me (in age)" },
        { "arabic": "الْعَالِمُ أَعْظَمُنَا عِلْمًا", "english": "The scholar is the greatest of us in knowledge" }
      ]
    }
  ],
